---
import '../../styles/services-pages.css';
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/base-layout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Website Development | Debrah's Digital Solutions">
  <div class="page-wrapper">

    <div class="page-header">
      <h1>Website Development</h1>
      <p>Modern, Mobile-Friendly Websites Built for Local Business</p>
    </div>

    <section class="service-pricing">
      <h2>What We Offer</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Custom layout and responsive design</li>
        <li>Business info, contact forms, service pages</li>
        <li>Image galleries, testimonials, and more</li>
        <li>SEO-friendly structure and fast loading</li>
        <li>Hosting & domain setup (optional)</li>
        <li>Training on how to update your own site</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="extra-info">
      <h2>Pricing</h2>
      <p><strong>Starter Website (1-3 pages):</strong> $350 flat rate</p>
      <p><strong>Business Website (4-7 pages):</strong> $600 flat rate</p>
      <p><strong>Custom Features (booking forms, galleries, etc.):</strong> quoted case-by-case</p>
      <p>Hosting and domain not included — we can help set these up for you.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="extra-info">
      <h2>Already Have a Website?</h2>
      <p>If your site just needs some TLC, we offer flexible update services — from adding new content and fixing broken pages to refreshing layouts and improving performance.</p>
      <p><strong>Website Update Packages:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Basic Edits (text/images, plugin updates): $40/hour</li>
        <li>Design & Layout Refresh: Starts at $150</li>
        <li>SEO & Performance Tune-Up: Starts at $100</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Whether it’s a small fix or a full makeover, we can help modernize and maintain your site.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="location-info">
      <h2>Ready to Launch?</h2>
      <p>Let's build something beautiful and practical. Call <a href="tel:7803309965">780-330-9965</a> or <a href="/contact">get in touch online</a> to start your project.</p>
    </section>

  </div>  
</BaseLayout>
